annotationA: Ada2a-containing complex component 2; H2A histone acetyltransferase activity; zinc ion binding; H4 histone acetyltransferase activity; histone acetyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: intestinal stem cell homeostasis; chromatin remodeling; positive regulation of histone H4-K16 acetylation; histone H2A acetylation; histone acetylation; histone H4 acetylation
annotationB: NuA4 complex subunit EAF3 homolog; Part of the Tip60 chromatin-remodeling complex which is involved in DNA repair. Upon induction of DNA double-strand breaks, this complex acetylates phosphorylated H2AV in nucleosomes and exchanges it with unmodified H2AV
